twister-core (0.9.29.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  [ Bernard Spil ]
  * Fix build with LibreSSL

  [ Chuck LeDuc Diaz ]
  * Use cppcheck
  * fix cppcheck syntax
  * organize .gitignore
  * multithread cppcheck

  [ Miguel Freitas ]
  * report the two local/external addresses we know about (which should be the
    same) in 'getinfo' rpc. i believe this should help debugging dht
    connectivity problems when we change networks, or router gets a new ip
    etc.
  * update ip_voter from upstream to get this nice maybe_rotate method. now
    the new ip can finally gain over a well voted old ip.
  * update registration network with the new external IP we learned from DHT
    peers
  * 0.9.29

  [ Kill Your TV ]
  * New upstream release

