twister-core (0.9.28.0+git20150310.r4934-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  [ Miguel Freitas ]
  * different id names per platform

  [ Ben Holden-Crowther ]
  * Updated license date

  [ Miguel Freitas ]
  * be more tolerant to detect outdated blockchain. the main problem with
    running libtorrent with an outdated blockchain is to refuse posts that are
    signed by new users. given this is only a temporary state (and most of
    users are older than a day anyway) it is better to be more tolerant
    instead of freezing up everything.
  * fix mistake reported by Tim Nicholson
  * fix #309

  [ Michael.X ]
  * fix memory size bug

  [ Dmitry Marakasov ]
  * Actually include sys/endian.h for le32enc/le32dec
  * Don't return NULL as bool

  [ sandakersmann ]
  * Added line break and "Core" to README.md

  [ Kill Your TV ]
  * New upstream git snapshot

