 -- Kill Your TV <killyourtv@i2pmail.org>  Thu, 01 Jan 2015 16:03:36 +0000

twister-core (0.9.28.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  [ Miguel Freitas ]
  * 0.9.28: better enforcement of DHT upload rate limit for non-locally
    generated requests. the limit applies to: DHT replies, refreshes of stored
    items, checking for status/tracker and proxy server. local requests (eg.
    dhtgets from the UI) are excluded from this limit, so user experience is
    not affected. in other words: we limit only the band contributed back to
    twister network for maintenance tasks.

  [ Kill Your TV ]
  * New upstream release

